        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 2:48PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Swartz to 8 miles south of
Jonesboro, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Claiborne, West Monroe, Winnfield, Jonesboro,
Brownsville-Bawcomville, Brownsville-Bawcom, Swartz, Richwood,
Chatham, Dodson, Calvin, Eros, Sikes, Vixen, Luna, Lapine,
Caderville, Fondale and Bosco.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
